# Directories Bazel must not descend into when expanding target patterns
# (e.g. `//...`). All are gitignored build/environment output, not source:
#
# - app/target  — Cargo's output dir. The Linux/GNOME build (flake.nix, Crane)
#   and editor tooling (rust-analyzer) write here. Bazel scanning it races with
#   rust-analyzer's transient temp dirs ("Failed to list directory contents")
#   and would otherwise also try to load any stray BUILD-looking files.
# - .direnv     — direnv's `use flake` profile, which contains a full source
#   checkout of this repo under flake-inputs/. Without this line `//...` picks
#   up duplicate targets like `//.direnv/.../app/core:ffi_test`.
app/target
.direnv
